  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d01fd2d64a9249049aaa77d5c12a82fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: Conclusion
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: 'CONCLUSION


    In this experiment, we learnt that- Glass tubes
    and rods can be cut to reduce it to a particular length. A triangular file is
    used to make a deep scratch on the glass tube, and then it is broken by applying 
    pressure on both of its sides. The jagged edges of the cut tube can be trimmed
    using a wire gauze. The method of fire polishing is used to round the edges of
    the glass tube.'
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: 'CONCLUSION


    In this experiment, we learnt that-

    Glass
    tubes and rods can be cut to reduce it to a particular length.

    A triangular
    file is used to make a deep scratch on the glass tube, and then it is broken
    by applying  pressure on both of its sides.

    The jagged edges of the cut
    tube can be trimmed using a wire gauze.

    The method of fire polishing is
    used to round the edges of the glass tube.'
